## Commands

- `make install` - install backend and frontend dependencies
- `make dev` - run backend and frontend locally
- `make check` - run static checks
- `make test` - run backend/frontend tests
- `make railway-deploy` - deploy via local Railway commands

## Code Style

- Backend: Python 3.12, FastAPI, Pydantic, Agno/AgentOS, PostgreSQL. Prefer typed FastAPI routes,
  dependency-injected mocked/Auth0-compatible identity, and owner-filtered data access.
- Frontend: Node.js 22, TypeScript 5.x, Astro. Keep interactivity localized to the `/chat` UI and
  avoid exposing raw hidden reasoning in thinking/progress states.
- Deployment: local-first Makefile commands for Railway; no GitHub Actions in this release.

